1780   /// Fuse two guarded fusion candidates, creating a new fused loop.
1781   ///
1782   /// Fusing guarded loops is handled much the same way as fusing non-guarded
1783   /// loops. The rewiring of the CFG is slightly different though, because of
1784   /// the presence of the guards around the loops and the exit blocks after the
1785   /// loop body. As such, the new loop is rewired as follows:
1786   ///    1. Keep the guard branch from FC0 and use the non-loop block target
1787   /// from the FC1 guard branch.
